fields.title: Backend Developer and AWS Solution Architect
fields.bio_md:
I write, test, commit, build AWS cloud infrastructure, collaborate, and deploy (a lot).  

With a background as a Paramedic, I pivoted into tech by completing ALXÆs Professional Foundations programùan intensive course that grounded me in agile teamwork, user-centered design, and problem-solving with empathy. Over 12 weeks, I built habits in collaboration, communication, and adaptability while gaining hands-on experience with tools like Google Workspace and project planning frameworks. This people-first foundation still guides how I approach cloud and backend projects todayùwith structure, curiosity, and impact in mind.  

After graduating, I advanced into the Backend, ProDev Backend, and AWS Solution Architect tracks (starting with the Cloud Practitioner program), earning certifications and sharpening my expertise step by step. Along the way, I developed hands-on skills in Python, API development with Django REST Framework and GraphQL, microservices, and cloud-native architectures. IÆve also built projects spanning web backends, real-time services, and cloud automation with Docker, Kubernetes, and CI/CD pipelines, while deepening my knowledge of AWS by designing secure, resilient, and cost-effective solutions.  

My passion for full-stack development, DevOps, and cloud architecture drives me to continuously learn and adapt to emerging technologies. IÆm not just focused on writing codeùIÆm motivated by building systems that scale, solve real problems, and deliver lasting value.

fields.title: Ecommerce AWS project architecture
fields.description:
AWS Microservices eCommerce Architecture 
This architecture leverages managed AWS services to deliver a scalable, secure, and responsive eCommerce platform.

User Access and DNS Resolution:
Users' DNS queries are resolved via Amazon Route 53, routing traffic to the application endpoints reliably.

Security and Traffic Filtering:
Amazon Web Application Firewall (WAF) filters incoming traffic to block malicious requests and protect the application from common web attacks.

Content Delivery:
Amazon CloudFront accelerates delivery of both static and dynamic content with low latency globally.

Authentication:
User authentication and authorization are managed by Amazon Cognito, enabling secure sign-in and user identity management.

API Gateway and Load Balancing:
Amazon API Gateway exposes and manages API endpoints, routing requests through an AWS Application Load Balancer (ALB) to backend services.

Microservices Infrastructure:
Backend services such as Product, Cart, Order, Search, and Commerce Tools are containerized and orchestrated using AWS ECS/EKS for scalability and resilience.

Data Storage:
Amazon DynamoDB is used as a fast, highly scalable NoSQL database to store product catalogs, cart information, orders, and search data.

Personalization and Recommendations:
Amazon Personalize delivers real-time personalized product recommendations to enhance user experience.

Event-Driven Interaction:
Amazon EventBridge handles event routing among services, enabling loosely coupled, event-driven workflows.

Data Streaming and Analytics:
Event data is streamed through Amazon Kinesis Data Firehose for aggregation and analytics.

Customer Engagement:
Amazon Connect is integrated for contact center services to manage customer interactions effectively.

Static Asset Storage:
Amazon S3 provides durable storage for static assets such as images and website files.

This architecture is built for high availability, scalable workload handling, secure user management, and enriched user experience through personalization and real-time analytics leveraging AWS's robust cloud ecosystem.

fields.title: Scalable and Secure File Storage Architecture with Amazon S3 and AWS Services
fields.description:
This architecture leverages Amazon S3 along with other AWS services to build a robust, scalable, secure, and cost-efficient file upload, storage, and sharing solution.

User Authentication and Frontend Integration:
Users securely authenticate via Amazon Cognito. The frontend is powered by Amazon Amplify, enabling quick development and deployment of scalable web and mobile applications with seamless integration to AWS backend services.

Content Delivery and API Management:
Amazon CloudFront distributes content globally with lower latency and high transfer speeds. Amazon API Gateway manages and routes API requests for uploading, downloading, and sharing files.

Serverless Backend Processing:
AWS Lambda functions carry out backend operations such as generating time-limited pre-signed URLs for secure, direct uploads/downloads to Amazon S3, enabling serverless scalability and reduced infrastructure management.

Secure and Durable Data Storage:
Amazon S3 stores user files, integrating lifecycle policies, versioning, and encryption via AWS KMS to ensure data durability, compliance, and confidentiality.

Metadata and Monitoring:
File metadata and sharing details are stored in Amazon DynamoDB. AWS CloudWatch and CloudTrail monitor system health, log events, and provide governance and audit capabilities.

Content Security and Data Protection:
Amazon Macie continuously monitors and discovers sensitive data stored in S3 buckets, helping detect potential data leaks and maintain compliance.

Access Management:
AWS IAM enforces granular permissions and security policies, controlling who can access and manipulate files and associated resources.

Advanced Content Analysis:
Amazon Rekognition can be utilized for intelligent image and video analysis, enabling enriched features like automated tagging or content moderation.

This solution efficiently addresses both frontend and backend needs, offering a secure, highly available, and scalable file storage service with intelligent content protection and fast global content delivery.

fields.title: ALX Django Learn Lab
fields.description:
A series of projects completing a comprehensive Django curriculum. This lab showcases my ability to:

- Develop secure and scalable web applications using the Django framework.

- Design and interact with databases using Django's Object-Relational Mapper (ORM).

- Build a complete RESTful API with full CRUD functionality using Django REST Framework.

- Implement user authentication and authorization systems.

- Apply security best practices to protect against common web vulnerabilities.

- Structure code according to Django's Model-View-Template (MVT) architecture.

- Prepare and build applications for deployment.

fields.title: E-Commerce RESTful API
fields.description:
A backend API built with Django REST Framework that powers an e-commerce application. The project demonstrates core backend engineering skills, including:

- Authentication & Authorization: Secure user registration, login, and JWT-based authentication.

- Product Management: CRUD operations for product listings with categories, pricing, and stock tracking.

- Shopping Cart & Orders: Endpoints for adding/removing items, checkout workflow, and order history.

- Scalability & Maintainability: Modular design with serializers, viewsets, and reusable models.

- Database Design: Relational schema with PostgreSQL/MySQL support and migrations.

- API Documentation: Interactive Swagger/OpenAPI docs for easy testing and integration.

fields.title: Chapa API Payment Integration (Django)
fields.description:
Implemented secure payment processing by integrating the Chapa API into a Django booking application.

- Built a Payment model to track transactions, amounts, and statuses.

- Developed API endpoints to initiate and verify payments with Chapa.

- Implemented background email notifications using Celery for successful payments.

- Configured environment variables for secure API key management.

- Tested full workflow in ChapaÆs sandbox environment, ensuring reliability and error handling.
